I don't know if it matters.  A querying agent will be asking for NS
records until it finds the correct server, then ask for an MX record.
The world will work regardless of which places you put your MX record ... 

&gt;From an administrative standpoint it is very very very nice to have
each piece of information located in only one place.  Your MX record
should be in the baz.myzone.stuff file rather than the myzone.stuff
file, or for that matter both files.  With it in the subsidiary file
you can spin that zone off to another server in a way which will allow
the people running that server complete control over the zone.  Otherwise
they have to coordinate changes in that one record with you.


